Peter walked forward into the cloud of green fog. “Come on out, Mysterio. Hiding isn’t very manly, you know.”

“Like you’d know anything about being manly.” Came the reply from somewhere among the fog. Peter huffed a sigh and continued onward to find his now, not an ally.

“I would. I actually fight and don’t hide away in a bunch of weird, green fog.” He shot back and rolled his eyes. This wasn’t what he signed up for when Nick told him that he was needed. He signed up for fighting villains with Mysterio. Not fighting Mysterio because he was one of the villains.

summary: “That doesn’t explain why I found you nearly dead by the side of the road in the middle of the night!”
question: “That doesn’t explain why I found you nearly dead by the side of the road in the middle of the night!”
answer:
“But Mr. Stark…” Peter mumbles, teeth chattering.

“No. No buts! You could have frozen to death, Peter!” Tony argued.

“I had to. That cat would’ve drowned if I hadn’t rescued him!”

Tony sighed, this was going to be a long night.
